<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Banquet2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Banquet,</orth> vb., 1) intr., to feast: <cit><quote>the mind shall b., though the body pine,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 25</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.6.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 6, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.6.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 6, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.1.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 1, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 77</bibl>.<lb />2) trans. to treat with a feast: <cit><quote>visit his countrymen and b. them,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 202</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>